Sentencas: Chemically stable composite BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta-Ni (BZY-Ni) was proposed and evaluated as the anode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: In-situ formed Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ@Ba (Ce, Zr)1-x(Sm, Y)xO3-δ core/shell electron-blocking layer towards Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ-based solid oxide fuel cells with high open circuit voltages

Sentencas: A thin electron-blocking interlayer was formed in situ at the anode/electrolyte interface when the anode-supported half cell was prepared via a high-temperature sintering process.
Titulo: In-situ formed Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ@Ba (Ce, Zr)1-x(Sm, Y)xO3-δ core/shell electron-blocking layer towards Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ-based solid oxide fuel cells with high open circuit voltages

Sentencas: Raman spectra and high-resolution TEM (HRTEM) results revealed that the electron-blocking interlayer consisted of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta@Ba(Ce, Zr)(1-x)(Sm, Y)(x)O3-delta core/shell-like grains.
Titulo: In-situ formed Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ@Ba (Ce, Zr)1-x(Sm, Y)xO3-δ core/shell electron-blocking layer towards Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ-based solid oxide fuel cells with high open circuit voltages

Sentencas: The Ba(Ce, Zr)(1-x),(Sm, Y)(x)O3-delta shell protected SDC grains from reduction and consequently the electronic conduction through the SDC electrolyte film was nearly completely eliminated in the new structured fuel cell.
Titulo: In-situ formed Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ@Ba (Ce, Zr)1-x(Sm, Y)xO3-δ core/shell electron-blocking layer towards Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ-based solid oxide fuel cells with high open circuit voltages

Sentencas: The fuel cell exhibited significantly improved open circuit voltages (OCVs), high power densities as well as good operating durability, demonstrating that BZY-Ni is a promising anode for CeO2-based SOFCs operating at a higher efficiency.
Titulo: In-situ formed Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ@Ba (Ce, Zr)1-x(Sm, Y)xO3-δ core/shell electron-blocking layer towards Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ-based solid oxide fuel cells with high open circuit voltages

Sentencas: These findings also imply that doped CeO2@doped Ba(Ce, Zr)O-3 core/shell composite is a promising electrolyte with high ionic transport number, which directs a new strategy to design novel electrolyte materials for SOFCs.
Titulo: In-situ formed Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ@Ba (Ce, Zr)1-x(Sm, Y)xO3-δ core/shell electron-blocking layer towards Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ-based solid oxide fuel cells with high open circuit voltages
